                          ------------
       dweep X11 Font: A mod of the Jim Knoble's famous Neep font
                https://github.com/DaisukeAramaki/Dotfiles
                
INSTALLATION:
1. Move the font to /usr/local/lib/X11/fonts/
2. Run mkfontdir, fc-cache -f -v 
3. Update fontpath in xorg.conf or .xinitrc, depending on whether you use a conf file for X or not.

Comments:
Just a few characters modded, the rest are the same as in neep. Looks good on netbooks with small screen real estate.

